# 詞: 銀包

1. 我個銀包細到連一張十蚊紙都放唔入去。 (My wallet is so small that it can't even fit a ten-dollar bill.)
2. 佢成日唔識儲錢，每個月收工銀包都係空空如也。 (He never knows how to save money; his wallet is always empty after payday.)
3. 去超市之前記得帶埋銀包，唔係又要返去拎。 (Remember to bring your wallet before going to the supermarket, otherwise you'll have to go back and get it.)
4. 佢個銀包雖然舊，但係對佢嚟講好有紀念意義。 (Although his wallet is old, it holds great sentimental value to him.)
5. 唔好意思，我今日忘咗帶銀包，可以借我十蚊買杯咖啡嗎？ (Sorry, I forgot to bring my wallet today. Can you lend me ten dollars for a cup of coffee?)
6. 佢成日話要買新銀包，但係始終都係遲遲未決。 (He always says he wants to buy a new wallet, but he never actually goes through with it.)
7. 個賊企喺地鐵站，專登留意行人嘅銀包有冇放好。 (The thief was standing at the MTR station, specifically watching to see if pedestrians had secured their wallets.)
8. 我個銀包入面除咗幾張舊紙幣，就剩低幾張過期嘅信用卡。 (Apart from a few old banknotes, my wallet only contains a few expired credit cards.)
9. 佢成日將銀包亂咁放，結果唔知掉咗幾多次。 (He always throws his wallet around carelessly, so he has lost it several times without knowing.)
10. 雖然佢個銀包入面冇幾多錢，但佢對朋友好大方。 (Although there isn't much money in his wallet, he is very generous with his friends.) [end of text]


